              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "4RUSJIA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " REPS (Resonance Experimental",
                " Transmissions and Cross-sections) exp.setup of Meson",
                " Facility at Institute for Nuclear Reseach of Russian",
                " Academy of Science. REPS setup consist of vacuum",
                " neutron guide,neutron collimators, filters-samples,",
                " radiator-samples, (n,gamma)-detector with B-10 and Pb",
                " shielding, neutron detector, spectrometric electronic",
                " equipment and measurement module with PC to accumulate",
                " information. Al, Mn, Cd resonance filters were served",
                " to define background in measured spectra and to reduce",
                " recycled neutrons with energy < 0.2 eV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "  Pulse neutron source RADEX (Radiational experiments)",
                "  of the Moscow Meson Factory (MMF INR RAS).",
                "  Proton energy 209 MeV, Ip=4 milliA, f=50 Hz.",
                " System of collimators as carbon and lead disks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Eight-sections liquid scintillator as aluminum",
                " tank of 40 l volume, 40 cm length, 40 cm diameter,",
                " with hole of 110 mm diameter; solution",
                " of scintillation admixtures of 50 g weight,",
                " 5.5 liter of methylborate B(OCH3)3 and 19.5 liter of",
                " toluene C6H5CH3 as scintillation liquid. For TOF",
                " spectra measurement as (n,gamma)-detector.",
                " Each section was viewed by photomultiplier FEU-110.",
                " Gamma-quanta (662 keV from Cs) registration efficiency",
                " 30%, geometrical efficiency 96%, power sanction about",
                " 30%. The signal amplitudes in each section were",
                " calibrated by high intensive gamma-lines from Co-60",
                " and Cs-137. Discrimination level in each channel was",
                " corresponded to the energy of gamma-quanta equal to",
                " 100 keV.  Placed  at the 49.3 m flight path."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " He-3 neutron counter at 51.5 m ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence multiplicities from pulses of eight",
                " spectrometric channels."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Flight path 50 m."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Transmission measurement for total cross-sections",
                "      determination.",
                " Resonance filters from manganese and cadmium for",
                " background determination."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Thin metallic disks of 80 mm diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Radiative capture reaction group cross-sections were",
                " defined from TOF spectra using normalization on",
                " U-238 standard cross-sections.",
                " Program GRUCON was used for group cross-section",
                " calculations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
